    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-04T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-04T05:00:00-05:00" n="311"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d311">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.796/577: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-04T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 4, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 4—8:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1767. See Embassy’s 1724, March 2, 8 p.m. We understand a telegram was sent last
                    night to the British Embassy in Washington proposing that preliminary and
                    exploratory conferences composed of British Commonwealth and India, Russia,
                    China, Mexico, Brazil and the French National Committee be held as soon as
                    possible at Marrakech. No preliminary discussions would be held in Washington.
                    We understand that it is contemplated that this conference would be followed by
                    a further meeting in which the other United Nations would be present.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
